Wallace LANDRY, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 6360. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. April 15, 1932. Claude L. Johnson, of New Orleans, La., for appellant. Edmond E. Talbot, U. S. Atty., John W. Harrell, Asst. U. S. Atty., P. Estopinal, and P. 0. Chavez, IJ. S. Veterans’ Administration, all of New Orleans, La., for the United States.

Before BRYAN, POSTER, and SIB-LEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
